<seg id="529">Another office had hung up a mailbox in a hallway that was not constantly monitored, in which some of the offers thrown in there even remained overnight.</seg>
<seg id="530">Since the throw-in slot of this mailbox was large and unsecured, not only employees, but also visitors to the office would have had the opportunity to extract and, if necessary, manipulate received offers.</seg>
