<seg id="572">Key audit results</seg>
<seg id="573">BRH</seg>
<seg id="574">Multi-eyes principle</seg>
<seg id="575">The audited awarding bodies implemented the requirements for the multi-eyes principle at the opening dates.</seg>
<seg id="576">They carried out the opening dates with negotiators and secretaries, who were not charged with any other award procedures.</seg>
<seg id="577">In the case of hands-free contracts with a smaller scope of services, however, there were isolated cases in which freelancers opened offers sent to them without the participation of the contracting authority.</seg>
<seg id="578">Minutes</seg>
<seg id="579">In the minutes of the opening dates, the opening of the offers was not always fully documented.</seg>
<seg id="580">In some cases, for example, the late-filed bids were not registered, in some cases even signatures were missing.</seg>
<seg id="581">Marking of offers</seg>
<seg id="582">The awarding bodies examined as part of the cross-sectional examination marked the offers in accordance with the specifications by a perforation with the date of the opening date.</seg>
